{
  "stem": "26576.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I-- we also spoke German, because it was very close to the German border, and my father dealt with-- with a lot of folks, Deutsche and Germans.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So German really was the third language.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This was the three languages that I spoke very early in life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But later on, on top of it came Russian, which I went to Russian schools.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then French, and now English.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I speak six, seven languages.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you-- one reads a lot now.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that stage, I really didn't have very much of a feel, because we didn't come in contact.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sosnowiec had 70,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And everything was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, I don't even-- I remember people say that the Poles were anti-Semite.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I personal, did not come in touch with it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "On contrary, when the war started, we had one of our neighbors, a Polish woman, helped me to buy tickets.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I'll talk about it later on when we'll talk about the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "No, I didn't have any unpleasant incidents in all my-- in all those years that I was growing up.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't remember anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So like I never had any confrontation with anti-Semitic Poles.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, my father was-- my father was-- really he was the founder of the trade union.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this was the Jewish trade union movement.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know much about the Polish trade union movement.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he was a founder of the Jewish trade union movement, which was, later on, in-- in Australia already, he wrote a book about it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was-- there was a lot, you know, like all those myths, the Jews are very wealthy, are really myths, because there was a lot of Jews that were very poor in Sosnowiec, that were working class people.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
